                <h1>What are Strings?</h1>
        <p>In C programming, strings are sequences of characters terminated by a null character ('\0'). They are typically used to represent text.</p>
        <p>Unlike some other programming languages, C does not have a built-in string data type. Instead, strings are represented as arrays of characters.</p>
