                <p>In C, you can represent strings using character arrays or string literals.</p>
                <p>A character array is a sequence of characters stored in contiguous memory locations, while a string literal is a sequence of characters enclosed in double quotes.</p>
                <pre><code>char str1[] = "Hello"; // Character array
        char str2[6] = {'H', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o', '\0'}; // Another way to represent "Hello"
